{
  "texts": [
    "This restricts their use of devices with limited memory.",
    "• Not optimized for inference As an encoder designed for language understanding, BERT performs slower inferences compared to smaller task-specific models.",
    "Its efficiency for production use is limited compared to optimized classifiers.",
    "• Limits batch size To fit in memory, smaller batch sizes must be used during training BERT compared to smaller models, making training less stable and slower to converge.",
    "While pre-training provides advantages, the enormous size of BERT results in computational constraints that restrict its application depending on available hardware resources."
  ]
}